The article announces several appointments and reappointments to various positions within the United States government. Jaime E. Esparza has been appointed as the United States Attorney for the Western District of Texas, replacing John F. Bash who resigned. Alamdar S. Hamdani has been appointed as the United States Attorney for the Southern District of Texas, replacing Ryan K. Patrick who resigned. Peter D. Leary has been appointed as the United States Attorney for the Middle District of Georgia, replacing Charles E. Peeler who resigned. Leigha Simonton has been appointed as the United States Attorney for the Northern District of Texas, replacing Erin Angela Nealy Cox who resigned. Jill E. Steinberg has been appointed as the United States Attorney for the Southern District of Georgia, replacing Bobby L. Christine who resigned. Martin J. Gruenberg has been reappointed as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation for a term of six years, and also appointed as the Chairperson of the Board of Directors for a term of five years, replacing Jelena McWilliams who resigned. Finally, Daniel I. Werfel has been appointed as the Commissioner of Internal Revenue, replacing Charles P. Rettig whose term expired.